				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The reason why you need to backup the registers on the stack in interrupt handlers is that interrupts can potentially interrupt your code at any time. If it would interrupt in the middle of a calculation like:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; LDA #$05<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;----NMI happens here<br />&nbsp; CLC<br />&nbsp; ADC #$03&nbsp; &nbsp;;calculate 5+3<br /></div>The 5+3 calculation will not work if the NMI clobbers A.<br /><br />For normal subroutines you have full control of when they are supposed to happen so you don't need to backup the registers.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

