				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I am often &quot;passing an argument&quot; to a subroutine using A,X,Y registers. And subroutines often &quot;return a value&quot;...usually the A register (sometimes just the zero flag or the carry flag is set or reset).<br /><br />For example, a subroutine that multiplies, might have the input as A and X, and return A = A * X.<br /><br />So, the original value in A needs to be overwritten by the subroutine.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
